President Trump traveled to Pennsylvania to deliver remarks on tax reform, joined by Secretary of the Treasury Steve Mnuchin, Director of the National Economic Council Gary Cohn, members of Congress, and representatives of the American Trucking Associations. The President emphasized the need for a tax system that is fair to working families and encourages companies to stay in America, grow in America, spend in America, and hire in America. He stated that tax reform will create middle-income jobs in industries such as trucking. To learn more about the America First tax plan, visit whitehouse.gov/taxreform.